item.title: PORTFORWARDING a wireless TEW-432BRP TRENDNET router? every ideas welcome (;
item.dc:creator: @dragon39990 dragon39990
item.description:
@dragon39990 wrote:

I can try to help, but I can help a lot more if you do teamviewer and I can just do it for you.
Legend: " "=What to type in ’ '=What to look for
start>run>“cmd”>“ipconfig”>‘default gateway’>----REMEMBER IT----
NEXT
Internet browser>go to your default gateway>DHCP client list>'what your computer is>‘your ip’
NEXT
‘virtual servers’ OR ‘ports’ OR ‘something like that’

Set your inbound and private ports to 43594-43594
-TYPE=TCP
–PRIVATE IP-set it to your computer number which you found in DCHP Client list
—Enable it
----Apply changes

If this doesnt work message me and go to www.teamviewer.com
get that program and I will look at it for you, and try to solve your problem.

~Dragon39990~
